Enobun Williams, Managing Director of JeroidNG, a leading e-commerce platform, has called on Nigerians who are crypto newbies to beware of scammers. Williams said that it is easy to get carried away with wrong information, and newcomers must beware of all sorts of platforms making promises that they are not equipped to deliver on. She said Nigerians must be educated about the business they are getting into so they can make their choices based on the information available to them. -Advertisement- “More and more Nigerians are choosing to hop on the cryptocurrency train as the economic realities of present-day Nigeria continue to bite deeper. So there are also a lot of fraudsters out there who want to take advantage of people who want to get on the train. “JeroidNG is one of few trusted crypto exchange and trading platforms that can help you begin your crypto journey safely and securely. Even if you are already making transactions and you want to take your dealings to the next level. “We are beginner-friendly and easy to navigate on our mobile App, we offer Bitcoin, XRP, Ethereum, and a couple of others at a very low fee with reliable customer support,” she added. The E-commerce giant boasts of over 100,000 subscribers using its platform to meet their trading needs. The platform also has a dedicated support staff that is on standby to help you through any problem. JeroidNG has grown from what started as an idea to a team of over 20 employees within its Headquarters in Lagos, changing lives and creating self-made millionaires—all with their trading strategies.